The defendant Francis J Coyle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Francis J Coyle is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
Defendant Francis J Coyle in court with attorney Aneeq Ahmad.  
Daniel A. Necci appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Attorney Haley Johnson also appeared for the State of Wisconsin later in the hearing.  
Matter is before the Court for Final pre-trial.  
Attorney Ahmad states there is not agreement in this matter.  
Attorney Ahmad is asking that Motions in Limine be scheduled for Thursday or Friday of this week.  
Attorney Ahmad is looking to exclude certain evidence.  
Court notes that the dead line for filing substantive Motions has passed.  
Court advises that if Attorney Ahmad believes certain evidence is not relevant, he can raise that issue at trial.  
State will have two witnesses.  
Discussion concerning whether defendant wants a Jury Trial or a Court trial.  
Discussion as to a Defense expert.  
Attorney Johnson has not received any information or reports from the Defense expert.  
Attorney Ahmad advises they do not intend to call him as a witness.  
Court takes recess to allow Attorney Ahmad to speak with his client about his intent not to call the expert.  
3:22 p.m.  Case recalled.  Court has colloquy with Mr. Coyle.  
Defendant is in agreement with the strategy not to call the defense expert as a witness.  
Attorney Johnson makes a record as to the two offers that have been made to resolve this matter.  
Attorney Ahmad advises the offers were relayed to his client.  
Court takes an additional break to allow Attorney Ahmad to discuss this further with his client.  
The Defendant is aware of these offers.  
The Defendant is also aware that if he proceeds to trial, the offers will be withdrawn by the State.  
Court will schedule this for a status conference on Friday at 1:15 p.m.  
Defense is to advise at that time whether they wish to proceed with a Jury Trial or Court Trial.  Status conference scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
